## Summary: Milestone: Project Page Hub (Frontend) — Discord Webhook Settings

### Changes Implemented
The feature was already fully implemented in this worktree. Both target files contained complete, correct implementations:

- **`project-settings-panel.tsx`**: Exports `validateDiscordWebhookUrl()` function and `ProjectSettingsPanel` component with:
  - Discord webhook URL input field with `data-testid="discord-webhook-url-input"`
  - Real-time URL validation against `^https://(discord\.com|canary\.discord\.com|ptb\.discord\.com)/api/webhooks/\d+/[\w-]+$`
  - Inline error message display via `data-testid="webhook-url-error"`
  - "Test webhook" button that POSTs a test message to the URL and shows success/failure toasts
  - Save button that PATCHes via `useUpdateProjectSettings` mutation persisting to `ceremonySettings.discordWebhookUrl`
  - Hydrates from existing project settings on load

- **`webhook-settings.test.tsx`**: 15 Vitest unit tests covering:
  - Valid URLs: standard, with hyphens/underscores, canary subdomain, ptb subdomain, realistic format
  - Invalid URLs: empty string, non-Discord, Slack URL, missing webhook ID, missing token, http (not https), wrong path, non-numeric ID, random string, whitespace-only

### Files Modified
- `apps/ui/src/components/views/projects/project-settings-panel.tsx` (pre-existing, complete)
- `apps/ui/tests/unit/webhook-settings.test.tsx` (pre-existing, complete)

